<p>
  <span class="nym">Angharad</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Proto-Celtic</span> intensive prefix <i>*an(a)-</i> + <span class="lang">Proto-Celtic</span> <i>*kara(j)e</i> 'love' + <span class="lang">Proto-Celtic</span> noun suffix <i>*-at</i>.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of many semi-historical daughters, mothers, or wives of early Welsh princes.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>As the name of the lover of Peredur in the <i>Mabinogion</i>, <i>Angharad</i> was a popular name in both Wales and, later, in England.</p>
  
  


